               <occupation type="political">Queen</occupation>
           <birth when="1889"/>
               
               
               <floruit notBefore="1911" notAfter="1962"> She was the wife of <persName ref="PRS5226haylase"/>, 
                  married to him in <date>1911</date>. She had six children with him, 
                  of whom only  three survived. The marriage lasted over a century and there was much sympathy between them. She was crowned on 
                  the occassion of her husband's coronation cermony in <date>1930</date>. Manan shared her husband's exile though having had 
                  a traditional education and not being acquainted with foreign languages she passed her 
                  public role in support of her husband to her Swis educated daughter, <persName ref="PRS8337Sahayha"></persName>.
                  
               </floruit>
               <death when="1962"/>
               
